lf42gtgq_2_jPvjfp_K1nQ
Since the departure of Taste of Philadelphia at 32nd and Camelback years ago this has been one of the only quality spots in Phoenix for a cheesesteak.  Personally, I've never ordered anything BUT a cheesesteak but my wife says the Uncle Sam's Special sandwich is awesome.  They have several locations, but I'm partial to the 32nd and Shea store for some reason.  It just has that slightly dingy feel that makes the steaks taste that much better.  The waitresses in knee socks and cheer skirts don't suck either.  Only thing missing is a full bar.

