My wife and I went for lunch yesterday.  Really cool decor, perhaps a bit much for some guys, but definite points for originality.  The Lunch menu was varied but not overwhelming.  The skirt steak looked interesting but we were told it had been eliminated due to prep issues, bummer.  Overall the wine list was disappointing, although I did like the concept of a few really special wines by the glass, although at $35 per we passed. Wifey had the Kobe Cheeseburger and I had Shrimp Scampi.  Both were good, although neither were memorable.   The service was terrific all around.   We'll check it out again for dinner...

